A MINI-BENCHMARK CREATED FROM THE SAT SOLVER PEARL

    "A Pearl on SAT Solving in Prolog", Jacob M. Howe and Andy King."
    In FLOPS 2010, Proceedings of the 10th International Symposium on
    Function and Logic Programming (eds Matthias Blume, Naoki
    Kobayashi and Germ√°n Vidal). Volume 6009 of Lecture Notes in
    Computer Science, pages 165-174. Springer, 2010.

===========================================================================

NOTES

  This version omits the parser and is limited to this set of files:

    chat_80_1.cnf
    chat_80_2.cnf
    chat_80_3.cnf
    chat_80_4.cnf
    chat_80_5.cnf
    chat_80_6.cnf

  The benchmark is also limited to the 'freeze' version of the solver.

PERFORMANCE

  The bechmark is compatible with the normal bytecode backend,
  optim_comp, and optim_comp+JS.

  The normal bytecode version (using a C-based engine) runs around 11
  times faster than the JS version (using V8 through Node.js).  Note
  however that the JS backend is not really very optimized at this
  moment.

